            . I am a <rs id="t18100718-78-viclabel472" type="occupation">post boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18100718-78-victim772 t18100718-78-viclabel472"></join>. On the 13th of July, in the evening, I lost my breeches out of the stable.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18100718-78-person776">
                  JOSEPH 
                  WRIGHT
               <interp inst="t18100718-78-person776" type="surname" value="WRIGHT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18100718-78-person776" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18100718-78-person776" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a horse patrol of Bow-street. On Friday the 13th of this month, my wife informed me that she had lost a waistcoat, two shirts, and a handkerchief, out of the garden at <placeName id="t18100718-78-crimeloc473">Edgeware</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18100718-78-crimeloc473" type="placeName" value="Edgeware"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18100718-78-crimeloc473" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18100718-78-off470 t18100718-78-crimeloc473"></join>. I had information also of the post boy losing his property, from suspicion, I pursued the prisoner; and apprehended him on Tuesday morning at three o'clock. On searching him, I found Hutchins's breeches upon him, and one of the shirts that had been taken away from my ground he had on; On searching the place where he slept in the barn, I found the other shirt and handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The property this man has been shewing to you, he found in another man's bundle, the shirt on my back, and the breeches, I was to give him six shillings for them.</p>
               <p>
